  <title>LECTURER IN MEDIA STUDIES (RADIO BROADCASTING) – (BOTSWANA CITIZEN ONLY)</title>
  <link>https://www.ub.bw/connect/job-opportunities/lecturer-media-studies-radio-broadcasting-%E2%80%93-botswana-citizen-only</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;LECTURER IN MEDIA STUDIES (RADIO BROADCASTING) – (BOTSWANA CITIZEN ONLY)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;a title="View user profile." href="https://www.ub.bw/user/2371" lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/2371" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" class="username" xml:lang=""&gt;mfetane&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Mon, 22/04/2024 - 08:29&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-department field--type-entity-reference field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Department/Faculty&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Media Studies&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Thu, 9 May. 2024&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF HUMANITIES &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;DEPARTMENT OF &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;MEDIA STUDIES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;VACANCY NO: IRC 1358&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Department of Media Studies in the Faculty of Humanities at the University of Botswana is currently seeking to recruit Lecturer in Media Studies (Radio Broadcasting).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Duties: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be expected to (i) teach graduate and undergraduate courses in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;radio broadcasting&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; (ii) take an active part in the supervision and assessment of undergraduate and graduate students’ research projects; (iii) serve on committees within the University and external professional organisations; (iv) carry out any other duties and responsibilities as may be assigned by the Head of Department.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should have: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; a PhD in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Media Studies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or related field&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; A Master’s degree in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Media Studies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or related field; (iii) a Bachelor’s degree in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Media Studies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or related field; &lt;strong&gt;(iv) &lt;/strong&gt;show&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;evidence of engagement in research.  (v) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hands-on experience in radio broadcasting, evidence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; of governance and social engagement in media&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; related fields&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;, as well as teaching experience at a University or comparable institution will be added advantages.    &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;N.B.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants with Master’s degree in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Media Studies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or related field with a Bachelor’s degree in &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Media Studies &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;or related field of at least 2(i) or equivalent may be considered under special circumstances. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB" xml:lang="EN-GB"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;: The University of Botswana offers a competitive salary and benefits commensurate with experience and qualifications.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; For more information about the University visit our website: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.ub.bw/"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;www.ub.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants are to address the stated qualification and provide other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position.  They should also quote the vacancy number of the post applied for, provide current CV’s (including telephone, telefax and email), certified copies of educational certificates and transcripts, names and addresses of three referees. Complete documentation should be sent to: &lt;strong&gt;The Human Resource Manager, Faculty of Humanities, Private Bag UB 00703, Gaborone, Botswana; Telephone: (267) 355 2641, Fax (267) 318 5098; E-mail: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:fohvacancies@ub.ac.bw"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;fohvacancies@ub.ac.bw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to:&lt;strong&gt; (i) Quote the Vacancy number and position applied for &lt;/strong&gt;and&lt;strong&gt; (ii) submit their references directly to the above address, before the stipulated closing date.  &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA" xml:lang="EN-ZA"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that applications with incomplete information shall not be processed.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted to Block 239, Office No. 121 (239/121).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;NB:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; 9 May 2024&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
