<item>
  <title>TEACHING ASSISTANT IN PUBLIC RELATIONS AND ADVERTISING (1 POST)</title>
  <link>https://www.ub.bw/connect/job-opportunities/teaching-assistant-public-relations-and-advertising-1-post</link>
  <description>&lt;span class="field field--name-title field--type-string field--label-hidden"&gt;TEACHING ASSISTANT IN PUBLIC RELATIONS AND ADVERTISING (1 POST)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-uid field--type-entity-reference field--label-hidden"&gt;&lt;span lang="" about="https://www.ub.bw/user/2085" typeof="schema:Person" property="schema:name" datatype="" xml:lang=""&gt;maribek&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="field field--name-created field--type-created field--label-hidden"&gt;Wed, 07/10/2020 - 09:36&lt;/span&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-department field--type-entity-reference field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Department/Faculty&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Media Studies&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="field field--name-field-tender-closing-date field--type-datetime field--label-inline clearfix"&gt;
    &lt;div class="field__label"&gt;Closing Date&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class="field__item"&gt;Fri, 16 Oct. 2020&lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-body field--type-text-with-summary field--label-hidden field__item"&gt;&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;FACULTY OF HUMANITIES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;DEPARTMENT OF MEDIA STUDIES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;TEACHING ASSISTANT IN &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;P&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;UBLIC RELATIONS AND ADVERTISING (1 POST)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;VACANCY NO. FH/ MS 7/2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;To provide support and instruction for Public Relations and Advertising in the Department of Media Studies, to work with the course lecturer in Print Journalism, Public Relations and Advertising courses and any other related areas as requested by the supervisor. Specific duties include guiding students in graphics design, the production of student newspaper, and other publications such as newsletters, magazines, fliers and posters. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Applicants should have: &lt;strong&gt;(i)&lt;/strong&gt; At least a Bachelor’s Degree in Public Relations /Media Studies/ Communication or related field with at least 2(i) pass / GPA of at least 3.6; &lt;strong&gt;(ii)&lt;/strong&gt; a strong background in public relations, advertising and desktop publishing; &lt;strong&gt;(iii)&lt;/strong&gt; teaching experience at University level, familiarity with Mac (Apple) operating systems and knowledge of Adobe In Design will be added advantages. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Each candidate must specify the area for which his or her application should be &lt;a&gt;considered&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Remuneration:  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;As per approved part time rates.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should clearly state the position and level they are applying for, address the stated qualifications and provide other information to assist the University determine their suitability for the position. Shortlisted candidates will be invited for interview. They should also provide current CVs (including telephone, telefax and e-mail), certified copies of academic certificates and transcripts, names and addresses of three referees, and send complete documentation to: &lt;strong&gt;The Human Resource Manager, Faculty of Humanities, Private Bag 00703, Gaborone-Botswana; Telephone: (267) 355 2041; Fax (267) 318 5098; E-mail: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:Tshoganetsom@mopipi.ub.bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tshoganetsom@mopipi.ub.bw&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; or &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="mailto:Tshoganetsom@ub.ac.bw"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tshoganetsom@ub.ac.bw&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Applicants should inform their referees to: &lt;strong&gt;(i) Quote the Vacancy number and position applied for&lt;/strong&gt; and&lt;strong&gt; (ii) submit their references directly to the above address &lt;/strong&gt;before the stipulated closing date.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt; Please note that applications with incomplete information shall not be acknowledged.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US" xml:lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Hand delivered applications should be submitted to &lt;strong&gt;Office No: 121 at Block 239 (239/121).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

